==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bull-roarer
<hw>Bull"-roar`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A contrivance
consisting of a slat of wood tied to the end of a thong or string, with
which the slat is whirled so as to cause an intermittent roaring noise.
It is used as a toy, and among some races in certain religious
rites.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bull's-eye</ent>⟦br⟧
